WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:07.341
[staff] What do you think you've gained
and lost as a member of SEVENTEEN?

00:07.424 --> 00:09.426
[♪ intense music playing]

00:10.177 --> 00:12.054
What I've lost...

00:17.601 --> 00:19.978
What I've lost?

00:25.817 --> 00:27.152
What I've lost?

00:33.825 --> 00:34.826
What I've lost?

00:39.623 --> 00:42.084
What I've lost? My joints, probably.

00:48.048 --> 00:49.591
What I've lost and gained?

00:59.059 --> 01:02.271
[WOOZI] What would I have lost
by being in SEVENTEEN?

01:09.778 --> 01:11.363
[♪ music fades]

01:11.446 --> 01:12.948
[♪ SEVENTEEN "CHEERS" playing]

01:19.371 --> 01:20.914
[indistinct chatter]

01:22.082 --> 01:24.751
[VERNON] It felt overwhelming
when we went on our first tour.

01:24.835 --> 01:28.589
But now, I just try to relax
and let things flow.

01:28.672 --> 01:30.507
Things turn out better that way.

01:30.591 --> 01:33.343
We don't get to stay for a month
or even a week on tour.

01:33.427 --> 01:36.263
We only get to rehearse
on the day of or the day before.

01:36.346 --> 01:40.309
The condition of the local venue,
any potential issues that may arise there,

01:40.392 --> 01:45.063
and even the weather and temperature
are our main concerns.

01:45.147 --> 01:48.734
We want to proceed as safely as possible
while still having fun.

01:48.817 --> 01:50.027
This is my job,

01:50.110 --> 01:52.404
so I have a sense of responsibility,
but it's also fun.

01:52.487 --> 01:54.531
Everyone, did you miss us?

01:54.614 --> 01:56.199
[loud cheering]

01:56.283 --> 01:58.368
[exclaims] Make some noise!

01:58.452 --> 02:00.620
[fans screaming, cheering]

02:00.704 --> 02:02.372
Whoo!

02:04.875 --> 02:08.337
SMALL WARNING SIGNALS
BEGAN TO APPEAR IN THEIR BUSY SCHEDULE

02:09.671 --> 02:10.672
[♪ music stops]

02:13.550 --> 02:15.385
-[staff] Is your stomach okay?
-[SEUNGKWAN] Yes.

02:16.678 --> 02:18.764
[DK] I'd be lying
if I said I wasn't stressed.

02:18.847 --> 02:20.474
Honestly, at this point in time,

02:20.557 --> 02:24.144
touring overseas
feels overwhelming quite often.

02:24.227 --> 02:27.189
We had to travel abroad frequently

02:27.272 --> 02:29.232
over the 10 years of our career.

02:29.316 --> 02:33.528
We're very grateful for everything,
but the flights are sometimes exhausting.

02:34.071 --> 02:37.074
Despite such concerns and weariness,

02:37.157 --> 02:39.660
I know this is a part of my job.

02:39.743 --> 02:43.330
And there's nothing I can do
but make the best of it.

02:44.915 --> 02:46.124
[SEUNGKWAN sniffles]

02:47.834 --> 02:51.296
[SEUNGKWAN]
The situation was rather complicated.

02:51.380 --> 02:54.591
That day, I broke down
as soon as I heard the first song.

02:54.675 --> 02:58.220
I was worried about the rest of the show.

02:59.137 --> 03:02.224
How am I going to get myself together?

03:02.307 --> 03:03.809
I guess I wanted to be comforted.

03:04.309 --> 03:07.521
I felt a little better after crying

03:07.604 --> 03:10.482
and getting comforted
by my members and the staff.

03:11.692 --> 03:15.487
I felt under the weather
when I woke up today.

03:18.365 --> 03:19.866
Well, I'll just have to see...

03:22.035 --> 03:23.120
how I do today.

03:23.870 --> 03:26.206
[DINO] We perform a show
for almost three hours

03:26.289 --> 03:28.583
at least twice a week.

03:28.667 --> 03:31.169
[DK] It's physically exhausting
and straining.

03:31.253 --> 03:33.338
Even more so
because we were missing members.

03:33.422 --> 03:36.800
The depth of the shows
feels different from the last two.

03:36.883 --> 03:38.093
It's not just SEVENTEEN.

03:38.176 --> 03:42.889
It's probably something
many K-pop artists face.

03:42.973 --> 03:45.183
[♪ SEVENTEEN "Super" plays over speakers]

03:45.267 --> 03:47.936
[S.COUPS]
Staying healthy is our top priority.

03:48.687 --> 03:53.775
We can't perform if we fall sick abroad.

03:53.859 --> 03:54.860
[♪ "Super" continues playing]

03:54.943 --> 03:57.612
♪ DARUMDARIMDA
Let's go to a whole new world, go ♪

03:58.488 --> 04:01.324
♪ In this rhythm ♪

04:01.408 --> 04:06.580
[MINGYU] Our shows build continuously
without a moment to catch our breath,

04:07.205 --> 04:10.125
so they are definitely
physically demanding.

04:11.668 --> 04:13.420
♪ I feel like I became Sonogong ♪

04:13.503 --> 04:16.840
♪ We never rest, every day
Make it, make it ♪

04:16.923 --> 04:18.633
♪ Let's take it to the end ♪

04:18.717 --> 04:19.843
♪ I feel like I became ♪

04:19.926 --> 04:21.636
[in English]
♪ I love my team, I love my crew ♪

04:21.720 --> 04:23.305
[in Korean] ♪ While we ran to this day ♪

04:23.388 --> 04:25.140
[in English]
♪ I love my team, I love my crew ♪

04:25.223 --> 04:26.850
[in Korean]
♪We can keep running some more ♪

04:26.933 --> 04:28.602
[in English]
♪ I love my team, I love my crew ♪

04:28.685 --> 04:30.020
[in Korean] ♪ Until we got to this place ♪

04:30.103 --> 04:31.188
[in English] ♪ I love my team... ♪

04:31.271 --> 04:33.565
[DINO in Korean] One change
I definitely noticed during this tour

04:33.648 --> 04:36.735
was that my body
started to feel a bit worn out.

04:37.360 --> 04:38.361
Let's do that again.

04:38.904 --> 04:40.113
Try it again from there.

04:42.991 --> 04:44.242
[softly] Oh.

04:44.326 --> 04:45.535
That's my best.

04:47.120 --> 04:48.413
-[exhales]
-[therapist] Five.

04:49.623 --> 04:50.832
-[exclaims]
-[therapist] Six.

04:51.583 --> 04:52.584
Seven.

04:53.502 --> 04:54.503
Eight.

04:55.462 --> 04:56.713
-Nine.
-[groans]

05:05.555 --> 05:08.725
[S.COUPS] I thought about
stepping off the stage over 100 times.

05:08.809 --> 05:12.813
But then again, I felt that
stepping down would mean losing.

05:12.896 --> 05:15.524
Dang it. Whatever. Let's perform for now.

05:15.607 --> 05:16.900
[in English] ♪ Fearless ♪

05:18.109 --> 05:21.029
♪ Because I'm fearless, eh, oh, eh, oh ♪

05:21.112 --> 05:23.198
♪ Fearless, eh, oh, eh, oh ♪

05:23.281 --> 05:26.952
[in Korean] ♪ What was I tormented by? ♪

05:27.035 --> 05:31.414
♪ Maybe I did it to myself, woo yeh ♪

05:31.498 --> 05:33.250
[S.COUPS] I'll leave just for a second.

05:33.333 --> 05:37.087
But then I'd think,
"No. Don't go. Hang in there."

05:38.588 --> 05:42.133
♪ Now, now,
I won't deceive myself anymore ♪

05:42.217 --> 05:45.846
♪ A new day, a new night
I'm reborn a new me ♪

05:45.929 --> 05:48.974
♪ I'll break through this wall
Today I won't be afraid ♪

05:50.767 --> 05:54.521
[THE 8] I've been experiencing pain
for a while now.

05:55.981 --> 05:59.317
Even if I try my best,

06:00.652 --> 06:03.989
health isn't something we can control.

06:05.115 --> 06:07.617
That was the most stressful part.

06:09.077 --> 06:11.079
[♪ "Fearless" continues playing]

06:12.455 --> 06:14.541
[JOSHUA] I can't give my all
from the beginning,

06:14.624 --> 06:16.501
although that's what I want to do.

06:18.587 --> 06:20.338
I can't stand. I can't get up.
[chuckles weakly]

06:20.422 --> 06:21.423
I'm just kidding.

06:21.506 --> 06:22.924
I have a feeling

06:23.008 --> 06:26.344
I'll look more uncomposed
as the show nears the end.

06:26.428 --> 06:30.432
I realized pacing myself
would be essential and that I'd do that.

06:30.515 --> 06:33.685
I go up on the stage thinking that,
but it never goes as planned.

06:33.768 --> 06:37.147
[in English] ♪ Gimme, gimme something new
Gimme something new ♪

06:37.230 --> 06:38.732
♪ Because I'm fearless ♪

06:40.483 --> 06:43.528
♪ Because I'm fearless, eh, oh, eh, oh ♪

06:43.612 --> 06:44.613
♪ Fearless, eh, oh, eh, oh ♪

06:44.696 --> 06:45.697
[♪ song fades]

06:45.780 --> 06:49.618
[in Korean] Doing a tour
always feels like running a marathon.

06:53.913 --> 06:57.709
[THE 8] My health has deteriorated
over the 10 years of my career.

06:57.792 --> 06:58.877
[♪ gentle music playing]

06:58.960 --> 07:02.589
I did martial arts as a child

07:03.131 --> 07:04.966
and even breakdanced.

07:05.675 --> 07:10.305
I've overused my physical ability
for over 20 years now.

07:10.388 --> 07:14.017
I've been taking arthritis medicine,
but it's not getting any better.

07:15.685 --> 07:19.105
♪ Kung chi pak chi
Kung kung chi pak chi, yeah! ♪

07:19.189 --> 07:20.440
[THE 8] My life is just a cycle

07:20.523 --> 07:23.652
of rehabilitation, self-care,
and working out.

07:23.735 --> 07:24.736
After that,

07:25.779 --> 07:29.282
I practice while feeling fine,
and the pain comes back after a show.

07:29.366 --> 07:30.784
It's a cycle.

07:30.867 --> 07:34.913
I'm the type who loses weight
when I get tired

07:36.081 --> 07:38.375
and exhausted on tour,

07:38.458 --> 07:44.297
so I keep telling myself
I need to eat well. [chuckles]

07:45.048 --> 07:47.967
I used to think
I had to push through the pain.

07:48.051 --> 07:52.931
But now, if I do,
I worry I won't last long.

07:53.014 --> 07:54.349
[♪ gentle music continues]

07:54.432 --> 07:56.559
♪ More and more... ♪

07:56.643 --> 08:01.606
My biggest concern is
not being able to do this for a long time.

08:02.732 --> 08:04.943
I think I'm just going with the flow

08:05.610 --> 08:09.948
in this tiny group called SEVENTEEN.

08:13.410 --> 08:16.246
I dreamed of many milestones,

08:17.080 --> 08:18.248
and they all came true.

08:20.750 --> 08:22.627
All my dreams may have come true,

08:25.004 --> 08:26.756
but I'll remain as a dreamer.

08:28.466 --> 08:31.219
I am someone who refuses to stay still.

08:35.306 --> 08:37.267
I think I'll continue giving it my all.

08:38.101 --> 08:39.310
[chuckling] Yes.

08:39.394 --> 08:44.274
EVEN IN UNCERTAINTY,
THE MEMBERS FIND THEIR OWN ANSWERS

08:48.737 --> 08:50.447
-[DINO] This is nice.
-[MINGYU in English] Oh my gosh.

08:50.530 --> 08:51.781
Best of the cities.

08:53.616 --> 08:56.786
[in Korean] Let me get changed
to feel that local vibe.

08:56.870 --> 08:59.205
It may be a bit showy,
but please understand.

08:59.956 --> 09:02.417
[trainer] Two, three.

09:02.500 --> 09:04.919
Six. Hold for five seconds.

09:05.003 --> 09:06.129
Shoulders locked. Seven.

09:06.963 --> 09:08.381
Again, seven.

09:09.257 --> 09:11.801
That's it. Nice. Let's finish strong.

09:11.885 --> 09:13.553
-[DINO in English] Last one?
-[trainer in Korean] Yes!

09:13.636 --> 09:14.846
Squeeze the weights.

09:14.929 --> 09:17.807
[MINGYU] I'm grateful to my fans
for making me who I am.

09:18.558 --> 09:19.809
They mean so much to me.

09:20.810 --> 09:23.438
But am I someone
who's able to enjoy the process?

09:23.521 --> 09:26.066
Yes, I am. I know how to feel content.

09:35.742 --> 09:37.160
[in English] Hey!

09:37.827 --> 09:38.953
[in Korean] How do you say "empty"?

09:39.037 --> 09:41.206
[in English] Empty. Empty area.

09:41.289 --> 09:43.041
-[woman] Empty space?
-Empty space. Yes.

09:43.124 --> 09:44.584
[laughs]

09:44.667 --> 09:46.377
-[in Korean] SEUNGKWAN's good.
-[DINO] He is.

09:46.461 --> 09:47.504
He's doing so well.

09:47.587 --> 09:49.547
[in English] Do you know SEVENTEEN? Huh?

09:49.631 --> 09:50.840
-A song.
-A song?

09:50.924 --> 09:52.509
-[in Korean] A song.
-A song?

09:52.592 --> 09:54.302
-[in English] "MAESTRO"?
-"MAESTRO"? Right. [chuckles]

09:54.385 --> 09:55.637
-No way!
-"MAESTRO"? Right.

09:55.720 --> 09:57.013
-No way!
-Oh my God!

09:57.097 --> 09:58.098
-Really?
-Yes.

09:59.057 --> 10:01.768
-[♪ vocalizing]
-Oh, yeah!

10:01.851 --> 10:03.311
-[woman] No way.
-Do you like K-pop?

10:03.394 --> 10:04.771
-[woman] Yes, I like it.
-Really?

10:04.854 --> 10:06.106
What's your favorite group?

10:06.189 --> 10:08.024
-Um...
-[whispers] Say SEVENTEEN.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.359
[woman] SEVENTEEN.

10:09.442 --> 10:10.735
-Yes!
-Hah!

10:10.819 --> 10:12.612
No way. Really?

10:12.695 --> 10:15.156
[SEUNGKWAN in Korean]
I'm not happy all the time.

10:15.240 --> 10:18.493
I'm a bit of an emotional rollercoaster.

10:18.576 --> 10:21.538
I think I'm someone
who knows how to appreciate

10:21.621 --> 10:24.165
and be thankful
for the small, everyday things.

10:24.249 --> 10:27.377
I can't just say,
"I'm totally happy right now!"

10:27.460 --> 10:30.004
But I think I'm someone
who tries to find happiness

10:30.088 --> 10:32.465
in as many things as possible, yes.

10:34.843 --> 10:40.390
I just sit around
if I stay in the hotel all day.

10:40.473 --> 10:44.352
But I get more energy
when I come out like this,

10:44.435 --> 10:48.231
when I see how lively people are

10:48.314 --> 10:50.525
as they go on with their lives.

10:50.608 --> 10:53.153
Seeing SEUNGKWAN play volleyball

10:53.236 --> 10:56.239
and getting a chance
to interact with children,

10:56.322 --> 10:58.741
those moments make us feel more human.

10:58.825 --> 11:02.162
I feel like we're more a part of life,

11:02.245 --> 11:05.331
not just here to put on a show and work.

11:10.420 --> 11:11.421
Okay.

11:12.672 --> 11:15.383
I think the beef will be ready
in a moment.

11:15.466 --> 11:16.467
[VERNON] Okay.

11:16.551 --> 11:17.969
Are you hungry?

11:18.052 --> 11:19.971
-[VERNON] I'm starving.
-[THE 8] Okay.

11:20.555 --> 11:23.099
[VERNON] I feel like
I live a life of abundance.

11:23.183 --> 11:25.059
I have enough time

11:25.143 --> 11:28.980
to do the things I want to
despite our busy schedule,

11:29.063 --> 11:30.231
so I'm happy with that.

11:33.151 --> 11:35.028
I'm on my way to buy some senbei.

11:35.778 --> 11:36.779
Senbei is

11:37.989 --> 11:40.658
apparently a snack or a meal for the deer.

11:40.742 --> 11:42.076
[indistinct chatter]

11:45.121 --> 11:46.331
I just wanted to try it.

11:48.917 --> 11:53.379
-I thought they were judging me.
-[staff laughing]

12:00.637 --> 12:03.973
[HOSHI] We've been doing this
as a group for so long,

12:04.057 --> 12:06.476
we don't know
what new things to try anymore.

12:06.559 --> 12:09.896
We came out in units like BSS and HxW
because the timing was right,

12:09.979 --> 12:11.064
so I can't not do it.

12:11.147 --> 12:13.274
But I think I'm in need of a break.

12:14.567 --> 12:17.487
I think I'm tired
of this overly stimulating world.

12:19.280 --> 12:22.450
At times, people get attacked
for the things that aren't true.

12:22.533 --> 12:25.870
So I want to step away
from this media world for a while.

12:25.954 --> 12:27.747
HIGASHISUMIYOSHI SPORTS CENTER

12:29.499 --> 12:31.251
[in English] Oh, nice.

12:36.256 --> 12:38.383
[members exclaim]

12:38.466 --> 12:40.343
[in Korean] No soba?
Do you want soba or tendon?

12:40.426 --> 12:42.512
-I can go if you're getting soba.
-Really?

12:42.595 --> 12:44.055
-Tendon is too heavy.
-Soba then?

12:44.138 --> 12:45.598
-Let's get soba.
-Let's eat soba.

12:45.682 --> 12:46.683
Do you want tendon?

12:46.766 --> 12:48.851
-I do, but let's get soba.
-All right.

12:48.935 --> 12:50.687
-[SEUNGKWAN] All right.
-[MINGYU] Okay, then.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.397
No more excuses.

12:52.480 --> 12:54.816
Let's play two rounds
and go by the win rate.

12:54.899 --> 12:57.277
-Yes. Let's go with the win rate.
-All right.

12:58.528 --> 12:59.529
[staff] Good grief.

13:00.113 --> 13:01.406
[SEUNGKWAN exclaims]

13:02.073 --> 13:05.034
I want to paint at home
and also travel places.

13:05.118 --> 13:08.079
I have to study English and Japanese
and work out too.

13:08.162 --> 13:11.499
But I have to fit everything
into the spare moments of my schedule.

13:11.582 --> 13:14.502
That's why life feels so hectic right now.

13:14.585 --> 13:17.255
When I do find the time,
that is my way of relaxing.

13:18.715 --> 13:20.842
I have to rest and take a break like that.

13:20.925 --> 13:23.428
So that I'll get motivated
to come and work again.

13:25.680 --> 13:27.432
Instead of forcing myself to work,

13:27.515 --> 13:30.518
I want to be someone
who knows how to rest when necessary.

13:33.521 --> 13:35.148
-[exclaims in frustration]
-[members laugh]

13:35.231 --> 13:36.399
[members] Good game.

13:36.482 --> 13:38.735
Gosh. Jeez. That was crazy.

13:40.111 --> 13:41.612
Stop filming. I'm embarrassed.

13:42.405 --> 13:43.823
[SEUNGKWAN] That was a good game.

13:43.906 --> 13:45.450
When I'm touring overseas,

13:46.409 --> 13:49.412
there comes a moment
when I don't even know where I am,

13:49.495 --> 13:50.830
when things get too busy.

13:50.913 --> 13:52.999
[♪ JOSHUA "Fortunate Change" playing]

13:54.208 --> 13:57.295
[WONWOO] About two years ago,

13:57.378 --> 13:59.005
I began to think it was a shame

13:59.088 --> 14:02.633
to spend my off days stuck inside my room.

14:09.891 --> 14:14.062
Sometimes, I plan a full day
with no wiggle room,

14:15.897 --> 14:18.983
and sometimes, I just wander aimlessly.

14:22.361 --> 14:24.280
I do my best to enjoy
the local atmosphere.

14:26.574 --> 14:28.409
I brought it to take some photos.

14:30.161 --> 14:31.954
They'll turn out great in this weather.

14:36.709 --> 14:38.044
-[staff] Wow.
-[server] Gnocchi.

14:41.923 --> 14:43.299
A tour should be like this.

14:45.093 --> 14:47.053
We've been way too busy until now.

15:04.695 --> 15:05.696
[camera clicks]

15:08.366 --> 15:13.121
[WONWOO] I need to learn
how to empty myself to accept new things.

15:13.704 --> 15:16.124
But none of us learned
how to empty ourselves.

15:16.207 --> 15:17.208
So...

15:17.291 --> 15:18.543
[staff] One, two, three...

15:18.626 --> 15:19.877
Thank you.

15:20.878 --> 15:22.296
[WONWOO] After getting some rest,

15:22.380 --> 15:25.883
we'll naturally return
with new things we want to do.

15:28.344 --> 15:32.014
If we do, I'm sure we'll grow even more.

15:43.776 --> 15:45.695
[VERNON] One, two, three.

15:47.155 --> 15:50.116
[WOOZI] All I want is for my boys

15:50.199 --> 15:52.827
to stick together without fighting.

15:53.369 --> 15:54.453
Finding pebbles.

15:54.537 --> 15:55.788
[HOSHI] There are five of them.

15:55.872 --> 15:59.000
-Did you say they were big?
-[HOSHI] Yes, it's like this big.

15:59.083 --> 16:00.376
Why can't I find any?

16:02.003 --> 16:03.588
I feel nauseous.

16:04.797 --> 16:05.798
Okay!

16:05.882 --> 16:07.008
It's huge. Let me see.

16:07.091 --> 16:08.134
Yes, I told you.

16:08.217 --> 16:09.385
I found it, DINO! [laughs]

16:09.468 --> 16:10.553
[members laughing, clapping]

16:10.636 --> 16:13.848
All right!
VERNON was the last to pick it up!

16:13.931 --> 16:16.559
-What?
-Everyone, splash him!

16:16.642 --> 16:17.852
[MINGYU] Our fire is still burning.

16:17.935 --> 16:20.396
I hope this warmth lasts for a long time.

16:20.479 --> 16:23.566
My heart is still burning brightly,
so I hope it doesn't go out.

16:23.649 --> 16:27.862
My reason for life now
is to live passionately

16:27.945 --> 16:29.572
and burn brightly like this.

16:30.281 --> 16:32.241
I think this is another new beginning.

16:32.950 --> 16:37.038
THEIR MUSIC DOESN'T STOP
WHEN THEY STEP OFF THE STAGE

16:39.207 --> 16:40.208
[♪ music fades]

16:40.791 --> 16:43.836
When I met BUMZU...

16:46.047 --> 16:48.841
the first thing I asked him was,

16:48.925 --> 16:51.636
"How do you punch in drums?"

16:51.719 --> 16:55.598
I was either in 10th or 9th grade.

16:55.681 --> 16:58.935
Our group wasn't supposed to be
a self-producing team,

16:59.018 --> 17:01.354
even just months before our debut.

17:01.437 --> 17:04.023
We were asked,
"Do any of you write music?"

17:04.106 --> 17:06.317
I said, "I do, as a hobby."

17:06.400 --> 17:08.569
They said, "Write one a week,"
and I said okay.

17:08.653 --> 17:11.239
They picked three
from what I wrote and said,

17:11.322 --> 17:13.449
"One of these three
will be your title track."

17:14.200 --> 17:15.201
"Really?"

17:15.284 --> 17:16.744
The three were...

17:18.829 --> 17:21.666
"Adore U," "Shining Diamond,"

17:21.749 --> 17:23.334
and "Pretty U."

17:23.417 --> 17:27.046
It felt like our debut
was suddenly being fast-tracked.

17:27.129 --> 17:28.839
[staff] It must've felt surreal

17:28.923 --> 17:31.509
to hear a song you wrote
come out into the world.

17:31.592 --> 17:33.719
That didn't even occur to me at that time.

17:33.803 --> 17:37.682
-[staff] Were you too young?
-Yes. I thought, "I guess this is normal."

17:37.765 --> 17:40.142
[staff] I feel like
HOSHI would've joined happily.

17:40.226 --> 17:43.020
-I did.
-[staff laughing]

17:43.145 --> 17:44.605
[WOOZI laughing]

17:44.689 --> 17:46.566
[staff] You must've been like,
"I'm on air."

17:46.649 --> 17:47.650
"I'm on TV!"

17:49.986 --> 17:52.989
I honestly didn't think
we'd do well when we debuted.

17:53.072 --> 17:55.616
"Will we make it?
No matter what, I'll try my best."

17:55.700 --> 18:01.205
I've always thought about this
even before my debut,

18:01.289 --> 18:04.375
but it never ceases to amaze me
that people like us.

18:04.959 --> 18:08.713
My family isn't that well off,
so where else would I go if not here?

18:08.796 --> 18:12.425
Back then, trainees who lived in dorms
didn't have anything in their pockets.

18:12.508 --> 18:14.427
We couldn't afford in-ear monitors.

18:14.510 --> 18:15.636
We couldn't.

18:15.720 --> 18:18.472
We had to ask our parents for help, but...

18:18.556 --> 18:21.183
It costs about 200,000 won, right?

18:21.267 --> 18:23.686
-[staff] They're expensive.
-Like good earphones.

18:23.769 --> 18:26.272
I thought, "How am I going to ask them?"

18:28.899 --> 18:31.652
-[WOOZI] The cheapest was 200,000 won.
-You're right.

18:31.736 --> 18:33.613
[staff] What's this heartbreaking story?

18:33.696 --> 18:35.698
At first, we used the basic earphones.

18:35.781 --> 18:37.783
[WOOZI] We used wired earphones
at music shows.

18:37.867 --> 18:40.620
Back then, I looked up all kinds of videos

18:40.703 --> 18:42.913
on principles I needed to follow
for success.

18:42.997 --> 18:45.833
You know, like "Making your bed
is the first step to success."

18:45.916 --> 18:47.585
I still make my bed to this day.

18:47.668 --> 18:51.380
They say, "Manifest what you want
by visualizing it 10,000 times."

18:51.464 --> 18:52.673
Imagining? That's easy.

18:53.382 --> 18:55.009
I thought that can't be real.

18:57.762 --> 19:00.431
IMBUED BY SEVENTEEN

19:00.514 --> 19:02.558
[MINGYU] MINGYU.

19:02.642 --> 19:04.602
[staff]
Picking the best-looking picture out.

19:06.937 --> 19:08.064
[staff laughing]

19:13.069 --> 19:16.781
I personally think
your natural yet chic movements

19:16.864 --> 19:20.743
are much more catchy than when you do

19:20.826 --> 19:23.454
complicated moves and try to look showy.

19:23.537 --> 19:25.414
True. I'm bad at complicated moves.

19:25.498 --> 19:29.210
It's not that you're bad
but rather that you're good at moves

19:29.293 --> 19:32.838
where you can control
the choreography's dynamics.

19:32.922 --> 19:35.466
All we need to work on now
is where we dance together.

19:35.549 --> 19:36.801
[DINO] Yes, that's it.

19:36.884 --> 19:37.885
[in English] Let's go.

19:37.968 --> 19:39.512
-[in Korean] It'll end in a flash.
-Okay.

19:39.595 --> 19:41.013
But as we do this...

19:41.681 --> 19:42.682
We can change it.

19:42.765 --> 19:44.975
-Let's make some formation.
-Let's do that.

19:45.059 --> 19:46.477
Well, I like

19:47.603 --> 19:49.021
those moments quite a lot.

19:49.105 --> 19:50.815
[♪ serene music playing]

19:52.817 --> 19:56.821
The things we do
when we are immersed in the present,

19:57.530 --> 19:59.031
the way we dance and sing.

20:00.700 --> 20:02.410
Not thinking, "What's the next move?"

20:02.493 --> 20:05.079
But something that comes naturally,

20:05.162 --> 20:09.583
dances, songs, and emotions
that come as easily as one, two, three.

20:10.918 --> 20:14.964
My dad taught me how to dance
before I could even remember.

20:15.047 --> 20:18.426
I'd choreograph whenever I got inspired,
film it, and upload it.

20:18.509 --> 20:20.970
It's as simple as that.

20:22.805 --> 20:24.932
It's like ABC to us.

20:25.725 --> 20:28.686
It feels natural,
and it'd be weird not to do it.

20:30.813 --> 20:32.481
I do it because I love it.

20:33.983 --> 20:36.402
Honestly, it's been difficult lately.

20:37.945 --> 20:39.363
Am I exhausted?

20:42.408 --> 20:44.869
There are some things I do out of habit.

20:44.952 --> 20:48.456
But I do those things
because my heart longs for it.

20:48.539 --> 20:49.665
Without that,

20:49.749 --> 20:52.835
I wouldn't have done it
even if I had 10,000 reasons to do it.

20:55.171 --> 20:56.797
I feel blessed often.

20:57.923 --> 21:00.384
I'm someone who must perform well.

21:00.468 --> 21:05.598
I want people to say,
"DINO's good at this and bad at that."

21:05.681 --> 21:07.099
"But he's the best on stage."

21:10.394 --> 21:12.104
"His performance is the best."

21:14.607 --> 21:15.608
[♪ music fades]

21:16.275 --> 21:17.276
That's what I want.

21:19.236 --> 21:20.321
I brought everything,

21:20.404 --> 21:23.115
including styles we never tried
and guaranteed hits.

21:23.199 --> 21:24.575
[HOSHI] New style and guaranteed hits?

21:24.658 --> 21:26.660
[♪ upbeat song playing over speakers]

21:31.081 --> 21:32.958
[in English] ♪ Idiot, idiot, idiot ♪

21:33.042 --> 21:34.126
Idiot, idiot, idiot.

21:34.210 --> 21:35.961
-[in Korean] It's like that.
-[in English] Idiot, idiot.

21:36.045 --> 21:38.214
[in Korean] We can use the word idiot

21:38.297 --> 21:41.634
-and be like, "Hey, you idiots!"
-[laughs]

21:41.717 --> 21:43.052
Something kind of playful.

21:43.135 --> 21:44.720
Or we can be the idiots.

21:44.804 --> 21:47.515
-[BUMZU] Yes, that can work.
-Troublemakers, fools, idiots.

21:47.598 --> 21:48.682
I'm an idiot for you.

21:48.766 --> 21:51.060
We are idiots. [laughs]

21:51.143 --> 21:53.354
-[♪ upbeat song playing over speakers]
-[♪ WOOZI vocalizing]

21:55.773 --> 21:58.484
Or we can change it like this.

21:58.984 --> 22:00.986
-[♪ BUMZU vocalizing]
-This is good.

22:01.070 --> 22:03.155
[♪ BUMZU and WOOZI vocalizing]

22:10.079 --> 22:11.789
-He writes lots of lyrics. Lots of raps.
-[laughs]

22:11.872 --> 22:12.915
[BUMZU] Yes, I know.

22:12.998 --> 22:15.209
When he's in the mood,
he writes like two, three a day.

22:15.292 --> 22:17.920
-I know. He shows it to us.
-Exactly.

22:18.003 --> 22:21.465
I don't know what it's for though.
It must be for his own amusement. [laughs]

22:21.549 --> 22:24.218
[BUMZU] And he likes to go around
getting feedback from people.

22:24.301 --> 22:25.302
[laughing] True.

22:25.386 --> 22:26.470
[BUMZU] "So? How is it?"

22:26.554 --> 22:28.347
-Now's your turn to shine.
-[BUMZU] It's now.

22:28.430 --> 22:30.349
-[chuckling]
-Keep writing more starting today.

22:30.432 --> 22:32.393
-I'm going to check.
-Okay.

22:32.476 --> 22:35.312
We just finished our show at Tokyo Dome,

22:35.396 --> 22:38.566
did a meeting for our group album,
our 10th anniversary album,

22:38.649 --> 22:40.150
and I'm finally in the car.

22:41.443 --> 22:44.071
Because of HxW songs,

22:44.154 --> 22:48.242
we asked BUMZU to come to Japan,
and he actually came.

22:48.325 --> 22:49.326
So...

22:50.744 --> 22:55.082
Tonight, we'll put together
the structure of the songs

22:55.165 --> 22:57.501
that has the potential
to be the title track.

22:57.585 --> 23:00.087
And as soon as we go to Korea,

23:00.170 --> 23:03.215
we'll probably record the song
as we write the lyrics.

23:03.299 --> 23:05.509
[♪ HxW "96ers" playing over speakers]

23:11.140 --> 23:12.141
It's good.

23:14.977 --> 23:16.353
And go all out from here.

23:17.104 --> 23:18.814
-Let's keep this part.
-We can do that.

23:18.898 --> 23:21.275
♪ Tiger's gaze, baby, I'm worth it ♪

23:21.358 --> 23:23.611
♪ Even if I overdo this
Don't stop me, Jihoon ♪

23:23.694 --> 23:26.906
♪ The newbies to the OGs
Became the OGs ♪

23:26.989 --> 23:28.157
♪ HOSHI and WOOZI ♪

23:28.240 --> 23:29.408
[♪ HOSHI AND WOOZI vocalizing]

23:29.491 --> 23:31.660
-[WOOZI laughs]
-Or from here... [humming]

23:31.744 --> 23:34.246
[rapping]

23:34.330 --> 23:36.790
-I'll begin with the first beat.
-[WOOZI laughs]

23:37.291 --> 23:38.709
[in English] ♪ You ready? You ready? ♪

23:38.792 --> 23:41.378
♪ Ready? Ready? Ready? ♪

23:41.462 --> 23:43.505
[in Korean] ♪ Try being like us
We're the same age ♪

23:43.589 --> 23:46.800
If this works out,
it's hands down the title track.

23:46.884 --> 23:49.637
Well, it was made to be a title track,
and it deserves that.

23:49.720 --> 23:52.097
The performers need to have fun
for this to work.

23:52.181 --> 23:54.141
Everyone involved should enjoy it.

23:55.184 --> 23:56.268
It's a lot of fun.

23:57.394 --> 23:58.395
[in English] ♪ It's stupid ♪

23:58.479 --> 24:00.189
[♪ HxW "STUPID IDIOT" playing over stereo]

24:00.272 --> 24:01.607
[in Korean] It's like house music.

24:03.108 --> 24:05.444
Nothing's set.
I don't know how it'll turn out.

24:05.527 --> 24:06.528
Well, but you do.

24:09.782 --> 24:10.950
It's very unique.

24:11.033 --> 24:12.910
We don't want to be a one-hit wonder.

24:12.993 --> 24:14.745
We want HxW to be

24:15.371 --> 24:20.584
a subunit that can last a long time,
artists who can do this long-term.

24:20.668 --> 24:24.296
We want both the music
and the artwork in this project

24:25.714 --> 24:26.882
to be high in quality.

24:26.966 --> 24:29.051
[HOSHI] ♪ Do it like us, just like that ♪

24:29.134 --> 24:30.970
♪ Tiger's gaze, baby, I'm worth it ♪

24:31.053 --> 24:33.806
♪ Even if I overdo this
Don't stop me, Jihoon ♪

24:33.889 --> 24:36.016
♪ The newbies to the OGs
Became the OGs ♪

24:36.100 --> 24:38.519
♪ High goes the airplane
It's HOSHI and WOOZI ♪

24:38.602 --> 24:40.437
-♪ When we're together ♪
-♪ We be pouring ♪

24:40.521 --> 24:42.898
♪ We met back when we were kids
in eighth grade ♪

24:42.982 --> 24:45.150
♪ We may make money
We never business ♪

24:45.234 --> 24:47.569
♪ Oh, such great harmony
Baby, just like this ♪

24:49.113 --> 24:50.447
-I didn't press record?
-[laughter]

24:50.531 --> 24:51.532
-Okay.
-[BUMZU] Sorry.

24:51.615 --> 24:52.700
It's okay. I got this.

24:52.783 --> 24:55.828
[♪ BSS "CBZ (Prime time)"
playing over speakers]

24:55.911 --> 24:58.330
♪ Hey there, fill up my heart ♪

24:58.414 --> 25:02.501
♪ Full to the brim with youth ♪

25:02.584 --> 25:06.505
♪ BSS is your happiness
We're a pair of jeans ♪

25:06.588 --> 25:07.631
♪ A pair of jeans ♪

25:07.715 --> 25:09.758
♪ A pair, a pair, a pair of jeans ♪

25:09.842 --> 25:10.843
[♪ song ends]

25:12.803 --> 25:14.304
[members laughing]

25:15.180 --> 25:17.182
[panting]

25:17.266 --> 25:19.476
[HYELIM] I can see that
you guys are pleased.

25:19.560 --> 25:20.644
[laughter]

25:20.728 --> 25:22.354
-[SEUNGKWAN] It's fun.
-[dancer 1] It's the impact.

25:22.438 --> 25:25.065
-[dancer 2] It's so powerful.
-[HYELIM] You all look pleased.

25:25.983 --> 25:28.193
"Pleased." That's the right expression.

25:32.823 --> 25:35.159
[HYELIM laughing]
Why do you keep coming this way?

25:35.242 --> 25:36.577
You want to take a break,

25:36.660 --> 25:38.996
-but you can't stop till you get it right.
-[sighs]

25:39.079 --> 25:41.582
-I can't get this step right.
-[laughs]

25:41.665 --> 25:43.083
[DK] He wants to get it right.

25:44.585 --> 25:45.586
[huffs]

25:45.669 --> 25:47.880
[SEUNGKWAN] This is the last one.
Give it all you got!

25:47.963 --> 25:49.006
[members] Let's go!

25:49.089 --> 25:50.924
-[DK] We got this!
-[cheers]

25:51.008 --> 25:54.219
[♪ BSS "CBZ (Prime time)" playing]
♪ Your happiness, we're a pair of jeans ♪

25:54.303 --> 25:55.304
♪ A pair of jeans ♪

25:55.387 --> 25:58.098
♪ A pair, a pair, a pair of jeans ♪

25:58.974 --> 26:01.727
We have a lot of practicing to do
when we get back to Korea.

26:02.269 --> 26:04.271
-The footwork is the issue.
-[HYELIM] It's hard.

26:04.354 --> 26:06.065
[DK] It really wasn't easy.

26:06.148 --> 26:08.067
We only have a day in Korea,

26:08.150 --> 26:12.488
so I'll have to really lock in
and practice then.

26:13.781 --> 26:15.991
I'm having a bit of a breakdown.
[chuckles]

26:16.075 --> 26:21.997
I'll learn it by heart and perform well
at the music video shoot.

26:22.998 --> 26:23.999
I got this.

26:25.125 --> 26:26.126
Let's do it.

26:27.252 --> 26:28.420
Good work today.

26:33.133 --> 26:37.262
I felt a tingle in my heart yesterday
as soon as we began the dance practice.

26:37.346 --> 26:40.641
Because I started to feel excited
about shooting the music video.

26:40.724 --> 26:41.934
-Your youth...
-Your youth...

26:42.017 --> 26:43.310
Youth is right now.

26:43.852 --> 26:45.896
-BSS is...
-Coming to you.

26:45.979 --> 26:47.314
[crowd cheers]

26:47.397 --> 26:50.317
[fans] BSS! BSS!

26:51.819 --> 26:53.362
People will be moved by this.

26:54.196 --> 26:55.906
Is this the first teaser?

26:55.989 --> 26:58.951
-The music video isn't out, right?
-No, we're working on it.

26:59.034 --> 27:00.744
When will the promotion begin?

27:00.828 --> 27:01.912
[director] Next week.

27:02.454 --> 27:04.748
[HYELIM] Already?
We didn't even practice yet.

27:04.832 --> 27:07.334
[groaning dramatically]
I suddenly feel so anxious.

27:07.417 --> 27:10.796
[staff] We were going to go
on a campaign trail on comeback day

27:10.879 --> 27:14.716
but decided not to
because of the political situation.

27:14.800 --> 27:18.220
We also had to cancel
a lot of our promotions, right?

27:18.303 --> 27:19.304
And so,

27:19.388 --> 27:21.932
that's canceled,
and the highlight medley...

27:22.015 --> 27:23.767
-[DK] The highlight medley?
-[HYELIM] It's off?

27:23.851 --> 27:25.435
We're not releasing that?

27:26.228 --> 27:28.939
[HOSHI] Are you serious?
We already filmed everything.

27:29.898 --> 27:31.066
[SEUNGKWAN] Wait.

27:31.149 --> 27:34.152
-I'm so angry right now.
-[HYELIM] He doesn't mean with you.

27:34.236 --> 27:36.029
-[staff] No offense taken.
-[laughs]

27:36.113 --> 27:38.532
-So we have to figure it out.
-[SEUNGKWAN] But why now?

27:38.615 --> 27:41.159
We already had a meeting about this.

27:41.243 --> 27:43.370
We went through this at the concert too.

27:43.453 --> 27:45.664
They know what their contents is.

27:45.747 --> 27:48.584
And honestly, they know better
whether it's risky or not

27:48.667 --> 27:50.586
since they have their necks on the line.

27:50.669 --> 27:54.590
And they don't think
people will bash them over this.

27:54.673 --> 27:57.968
But the agency isn't sure
if we should drop this or not.

27:58.051 --> 28:00.888
They were just left hanging.
That's why they're mad.

28:00.971 --> 28:04.224
We put so much work
into preparing and practicing for this.

28:04.308 --> 28:07.936
They already said it wouldn't be a problem
and that we could drop it.

28:08.020 --> 28:10.522
This is what they're saying now.
We'll sort it out.

28:14.192 --> 28:17.279
We had kept our fans waiting,
and we were also thinking,

28:18.322 --> 28:20.991
"Can't we do it? We want to."

28:21.074 --> 28:24.161
We put a lot of work into this,
and we knew it'd be great.

28:24.244 --> 28:26.538
I hoped we would go as planned.

28:26.622 --> 28:28.832
After all, we didn't mean
anything political by it.

28:28.916 --> 28:33.086
At the time, we were just worried
that everything we worked for

28:33.170 --> 28:36.089
might disappear into thin air.

28:38.216 --> 28:40.636
[♪ SEUNGKWAN "Raindrops"
playing over speakers]

28:50.312 --> 28:52.522
[SEUNGKWAN] I think
I always give it my all.

28:52.606 --> 28:55.317
-[♪ song stops]
-It's already sounding so good.

28:55.400 --> 28:58.236
Someone who tries so hard
even when he isn't told to.

28:58.987 --> 29:00.530
That's me, and I don't hate that.

29:00.614 --> 29:01.698
[♪ SEUNGKWAN "Raindrops" playing]

29:02.282 --> 29:04.952
[SEUNGKWAN] ♪ A song of some day ♪

29:05.535 --> 29:08.372
♪ Pours down some more ♪

29:08.956 --> 29:12.376
♪ And disappears again ♪

29:14.419 --> 29:19.591
♪ Actually, I'm heading to you... ♪

29:19.675 --> 29:20.676
[clears throat]

29:20.801 --> 29:25.138
I don't think
we can decide on the song today.

29:25.222 --> 29:26.890
-Let's give it more time.
-[director] Okay.

29:27.599 --> 29:28.809
Hey!

29:33.522 --> 29:34.606
[in English] Nice!

29:34.690 --> 29:35.691
[all cheering, exclaiming]

29:35.774 --> 29:37.025
[MINGYU in Korean] Good game!

29:37.109 --> 29:38.360
We're done.

29:38.443 --> 29:40.904
[staff] Pretend you're listening to music.

29:40.988 --> 29:43.240
Looking serious, like this.

29:44.700 --> 29:48.787
Self-love and self-respect

29:49.496 --> 29:52.082
are very important and necessary.

29:55.794 --> 29:57.838
How much of my endeavors

29:58.463 --> 30:01.717
are moving people's hearts right now?

30:04.886 --> 30:06.304
♪ But it's okay ♪

30:06.388 --> 30:07.514
Is that it?

30:08.098 --> 30:09.099
Okay.

30:09.975 --> 30:12.769
"I only watch you"
needs to be softer, right? Okay.

30:13.687 --> 30:14.688
Okay.

30:15.355 --> 30:18.191
I always need to check myself

30:18.275 --> 30:22.863
and objectively understand
what kind of singer I am today.

30:23.864 --> 30:27.576
I was going to raise it to 3C.

30:28.660 --> 30:31.496
Who did I think I was?

30:31.580 --> 30:33.665
What was I thinking?

30:34.708 --> 30:39.129
Am I doing this because I want to

30:39.212 --> 30:42.049
even when the public
or my fans don't like it?

30:42.132 --> 30:44.718
Am I just doing this for me?

30:44.801 --> 30:47.763
♪ I only watch you ♪

30:47.846 --> 30:53.810
♪ From my memories ♪

30:54.603 --> 30:57.647
It didn't look so great on Ungjae.
[laughs]

30:57.731 --> 30:59.232
CARATs, do I really look okay?

31:05.739 --> 31:06.823
Hello?

31:07.908 --> 31:09.242
What are you up to, Dad?

31:10.786 --> 31:11.995
[laughing] Really?

31:14.539 --> 31:16.124
You had one too many drinks.

31:17.709 --> 31:19.711
[♪ humming softly]

31:22.339 --> 31:28.178
I'm an artist that needs to study
and learn right now.

31:29.221 --> 31:34.976
I want to grow more
and challenge myself more as an artist.

31:35.852 --> 31:37.062
Yes.

31:37.938 --> 31:40.649
I want to be an incredible artist.

31:41.858 --> 31:47.948
♪ The way we changed hurts a little ♪

31:48.031 --> 31:54.788
[over speaker] ♪ But it's okay ♪

31:54.871 --> 31:56.248
[♪ music fades]

31:58.708 --> 32:01.461
SEVENTEEN WON THE ALBUM
AND THE ARTIST OF THE YEAR IN 2024 MAMA

32:01.545 --> 32:03.171
WINNING GRAND AWARD 2 YEARS RUNNING

32:05.757 --> 32:06.758
[MINGYU in English] Come on, yo!

32:06.842 --> 32:08.844
[people cheering]

32:08.927 --> 32:10.929
[♪ SEVENTEEN "Together" playing]

32:11.888 --> 32:13.306
[WONWOO in Korean] Good work!

32:13.390 --> 32:14.850
[DK squeals]

32:14.933 --> 32:16.601
-This is insane! Is this real?
-[laughing]

32:16.685 --> 32:18.854
-[JOSHUA] OMG!
-How is this real?

32:18.937 --> 32:20.438
[members] Good work! Great job!

32:20.522 --> 32:22.607
-[SEUNGKWAN] Thank you, everyone!
-[staff] Good work!

32:22.691 --> 32:26.361
[members and staff] Great job.

32:26.444 --> 32:28.238
Good work! Thank you!

32:29.239 --> 32:30.866
[members and staff] Great work.

32:31.783 --> 32:35.120
[members and staff] Thank you.

32:43.628 --> 32:48.133
Relax, but not too much.
Walk, but not too slow.

32:51.178 --> 32:53.180
[both grunting]

33:02.022 --> 33:06.902
[HYELIM] If you perform after 20 years,
we'll do one new song...

33:07.861 --> 33:10.113
-"VERY NICE"? [laughs]
-[HYELIM] ...and "VERY NICE."

33:10.197 --> 33:12.449
No, something cool like "Super."

33:12.532 --> 33:13.575
"Super" sounds great.

33:13.658 --> 33:14.659
[HYELIM] Wind down,

33:14.743 --> 33:16.244
-and then "VERY NICE."
-"VERY NICE."

33:16.328 --> 33:17.329
[staff members] Everyone!

33:17.412 --> 33:19.414
[laughter]

33:21.291 --> 33:24.211
[DK] There's light
at the end of the tunnel, everyone.

33:25.921 --> 33:27.839
That's our bright future.

33:31.509 --> 33:34.262
[staff cheering]

33:37.057 --> 33:38.183
Cheers, MINGYU.

33:39.476 --> 33:40.977
[MINGYU] Hey!

33:41.853 --> 33:45.565
Mmm! This yukgaejang is fire.

33:45.649 --> 33:47.067
-[DK] Is it?
-It's so good.

33:47.150 --> 33:52.280
[staff] ♪ Congrats on winning
the Grand Award ♪

33:52.364 --> 33:54.574
♪ Congratulations, dear SEVENTEEN ♪

33:54.658 --> 33:56.159
♪ Congrats on the Grand Award ♪

33:56.243 --> 33:59.162
-[DK in English] Make some noise!
-[staff cheering]

33:59.246 --> 34:00.705
[members in Korean] Thank you!

34:01.414 --> 34:05.001
This is the perfect timing
for someone to give a speech.

34:05.085 --> 34:08.213
-[HOSHI] Do it, DINO.
-[DK] DINO will make a toast!

34:08.296 --> 34:10.423
[staff cheering]

34:10.507 --> 34:14.302
-Great work today, everyone!
-[DK] Hey!

34:15.887 --> 34:18.640
-Please fill your glasses.
-Yeah.

34:18.723 --> 34:22.102
This is our second time
winning the Grand Award,

34:22.185 --> 34:25.772
but we wouldn't be here today
if it hadn't been for everyone here.

34:25.855 --> 34:27.190
[DK] That's right!

34:27.691 --> 34:30.944
Thank you for all your support
and great work today!

34:32.320 --> 34:33.822
Let's cheer in three!

34:33.905 --> 34:35.532
Chug!

34:35.615 --> 34:38.368
[MINGYU and staff] Chug!

34:38.451 --> 34:40.328
[DINO] We'll make a toast with "Let's go!"

34:40.412 --> 34:41.454
One, two, three.

34:41.538 --> 34:43.456
[all] Let's go!

34:44.624 --> 34:46.293
[♪ SEVENTEEN "IF you leave me" playing]

34:47.377 --> 34:49.671
-[HOSHI] He can't show his hair.
-[DINO] Take it like this?

34:50.255 --> 34:52.132
[staff] Look here. One, two, three.

34:52.215 --> 34:53.216
Okay.

34:53.300 --> 34:54.384
Doing okay, JUN?

34:54.467 --> 34:55.593
[MINGYU laughing]

34:55.677 --> 34:58.597
-[HOSHI] We're having dinner.
-[DK] Did you get there safely?

34:58.680 --> 34:59.889
[DK] Enjoy your drink.

35:01.641 --> 35:03.602
Okay. We love you.

35:04.311 --> 35:06.396
-Good luck with the shoot.
-[SEUNGKWAN] I love you!

35:07.939 --> 35:09.858
It's Shimizu.

35:09.941 --> 35:10.942
[JOSHUA laughs]

35:11.818 --> 35:12.819
Shimizu!

35:13.445 --> 35:15.238
[staff] Congratulations!

35:15.322 --> 35:17.157
-Congrats on the Grand Award!
-Congrats!

35:21.703 --> 35:23.663
SEVENTEEN AND CARATS
MAKE TONIGHT BEAUTIFUL

35:29.502 --> 35:31.212
[staff] Thank you.

35:31.296 --> 35:33.298
[members cheering, clapping]

35:41.765 --> 35:43.141
[HYELIM] We did 30 shows,
including Bangkok.

35:43.224 --> 35:44.225
We did so many.

35:44.309 --> 35:45.769
[HYELIM] Look. The photos look great.

35:47.354 --> 35:49.064
-[MINGYU] Great job!
-Seriously.

35:49.147 --> 35:50.607
Great job, guys.

35:50.690 --> 35:53.234
Looking at it like this,
we really did a lot of shows.

35:53.318 --> 35:57.113
I could see that we tried our best
to meet our fans, CARATs.

35:57.197 --> 36:01.534
I realized how much we had achieved
when I saw those pictures.

36:01.618 --> 36:04.954
We had put on a lot more shows
than I remembered.

36:05.038 --> 36:06.748
It was moving.

36:06.831 --> 36:10.293
When I saw the cities,
I remembered the memories we made,

36:10.377 --> 36:13.171
the food we had eaten there,

36:13.254 --> 36:15.507
and the things we did as a group.

36:15.590 --> 36:17.050
Despite challenging situations,

36:17.801 --> 36:21.763
I was proud of us
for holding so many shows.

36:21.846 --> 36:24.140
I felt proud, but it was heartrending too.

36:24.224 --> 36:25.308
It really wasn't easy.

36:25.392 --> 36:26.726
It's enjoyable when it is.

36:26.810 --> 36:29.312
We have fun when we can,
and then we put on a show.

36:29.396 --> 36:30.730
But when we're on a tour,

36:30.814 --> 36:35.860
it's physically straining,
and our health problems begin to arise.

36:35.944 --> 36:38.780
But when I saw the photos,
I only recalled the good times.

36:38.863 --> 36:40.865
So I felt relieved and happy.

36:40.949 --> 36:42.826
[crowd cheering]

36:42.909 --> 36:44.869
-[MINGYU] Yay.
-[DINO] Come here, 218 bro.

36:45.578 --> 36:46.579
[MINGYU] 218 bro.

36:46.663 --> 36:50.166
[WONWOO] For the last photo
of the RIGHT HERE WORLD TOUR,

36:50.250 --> 36:52.752
let's put DK and VERNON in the middle.

36:52.836 --> 36:54.129
[DINO in English] One more!

36:54.212 --> 36:55.672
One, two, three.

36:55.755 --> 36:56.756
[in Korean] Click!

36:57.882 --> 37:01.052
[VERNON] I truly hope
we were able to bring you happiness,

37:01.136 --> 37:04.347
even for a moment,

37:04.431 --> 37:07.934
and we'll do our best to keep doing so.

37:08.017 --> 37:09.185
[DINO] They prepared a slogan.

37:09.269 --> 37:11.813
[HOSHI and DK] SEVENTEEN and CARATs
make tonight beautiful.

37:11.896 --> 37:13.732
[in English] ♪ Oh yes, I'm that diamond ♪

37:13.815 --> 37:16.025
[in Korean] ♪ The one of a kind,
SEVENTEEN CARAT ♪

37:16.109 --> 37:19.362
♪ Enjoy every minute and second
Because time is precious like a jewel ♪

37:19.446 --> 37:20.780
[in English] ♪ This is your life, hun ♪

37:20.864 --> 37:22.365
[HOSHI in Korean]
Why don't we start the encore?

37:22.449 --> 37:23.950
[translator speaking in Thai]

37:24.033 --> 37:25.660
[in English] Everybody, stand up!

37:25.744 --> 37:27.704
[in Korean] "VERY NICE!"

37:27.787 --> 37:29.372
♪ Very nice ♪

37:29.456 --> 37:31.332
[♪ SEVENTEEN "VERY NICE" playing]

37:31.416 --> 37:32.834
♪ Very nice ♪

37:33.835 --> 37:35.587
♪ Feels, feels, feels nice ♪

37:35.670 --> 37:37.547
♪ Very nice ♪

37:37.630 --> 37:41.676
[SEUNGKWAN] We often compare
a concert to a marathon.

37:42.427 --> 37:46.181
I feel like I finished running
a full marathon, all 42.195km.

37:46.264 --> 37:48.057
[chuckling] There was a sense of relief.

37:48.141 --> 37:50.143
It felt freeing.

37:50.226 --> 37:53.605
I was so grateful that
everyone remained healthy until the end.

37:53.688 --> 37:55.565
I want to thank everyone who came.

37:55.648 --> 37:59.444
[MINGYU] It was the last show,
so we must've all hyped ourselves up,

37:59.527 --> 38:02.489
thinking, "It's the last one.
We did well."

38:02.572 --> 38:06.659
It's a shame that not all 13 of us
could take part in this.

38:06.743 --> 38:10.955
[SEUNGKWAN] Yet we ended the tour well,
with a great finale.

38:11.039 --> 38:12.248
It felt great.

38:12.332 --> 38:14.834
We'll return with a new look.

38:14.918 --> 38:16.377
[translator speaking in Thai]

38:16.461 --> 38:18.087
-[S.COUPS] We love you.
-Bye, RIGHT HERE!

38:18.171 --> 38:19.172
We were SEVENTEEN.

38:19.255 --> 38:21.216
[members] Say the name, SEVENTEEN!
Thank you!

38:22.550 --> 38:24.552
[DK] We had fun, kiddos!

38:25.512 --> 38:28.097
[DINO] This was the best show
of the RIGHT HERE tour! Thank you!

38:28.181 --> 38:29.516
-[S.COUPS] SEVENTEEN, CARAT...
-Clap, clap.

38:29.599 --> 38:31.434
[members in English]
SEVENTEEN, RIGHT HERE!

38:31.518 --> 38:33.186
-[in Korean] We had so much fun, guys!
-[♪ music ends]

38:33.269 --> 38:34.979
-[DK] I won't forget you, RIGHT HERE!
-[crowd cheering]

38:35.063 --> 38:36.356
[S.COUPS] That line was great.

38:37.106 --> 38:38.775
The concert is over.

38:38.858 --> 38:40.485
Great show!

38:40.568 --> 38:42.570
Get home safely, CARATs.

38:46.282 --> 38:47.283
Great show.

38:47.367 --> 38:48.368
That was amazing.

38:49.452 --> 38:50.954
We did so well.

38:51.037 --> 38:53.998
[MINGYU] Great job on finishing
all 30 shows. I'm glad no one got hurt.

38:54.082 --> 38:56.167
Let's share our beautiful music
with CARATs.

38:56.251 --> 38:57.669
-[HOSHI] Voice is an instrument!
-It is!

38:57.752 --> 39:00.421
[MINGYU] Great job, everyone.
Let's end this on a high note.

39:00.505 --> 39:01.548
[HOSHI] One, two, three!

39:01.631 --> 39:02.799
[all] Let's go!

39:02.882 --> 39:04.175
[MINGYU] One, two, three!

39:04.259 --> 39:05.593
[all] Let's go!

39:07.262 --> 39:08.596
[staff] Great work!

39:08.680 --> 39:11.015
[staff cheering]

39:23.695 --> 39:25.071
One, two, three!

39:25.154 --> 39:27.031
[all] A pair of jeans!

39:27.115 --> 39:28.908
[all cheering]

39:28.992 --> 39:31.286
-It starts off easy and gets harder.
-[laughter]

39:31.369 --> 39:32.495
It's the other way around.

39:34.455 --> 39:36.583
I'm so sad that our tour is over.

39:41.546 --> 39:42.839
I can easily do 30 more.

39:45.967 --> 39:48.636
[mouthing] Help me!

39:53.391 --> 39:56.394
I should go and say thanks. [laughs]

39:59.647 --> 40:00.732
Aw!

40:01.816 --> 40:03.318
MINGYU assaulted SEUNGKWAN!

40:03.401 --> 40:04.652
-Include this.
-This is...

40:04.736 --> 40:06.112
-Show it.
-[SEUNGKWAN] This is evidence.

40:06.195 --> 40:07.196
I don't mind.

40:07.280 --> 40:09.449
I'll use it as evidence when I sue him.

40:09.532 --> 40:11.451
-[MINGYU] "Aw!"
-[DK] Your weak scream?

40:11.534 --> 40:12.785
[MINGYU] "Aw!"

40:12.869 --> 40:15.788
"MINGYU assaulted SEUNGKWAN!" "Aw!"

40:15.872 --> 40:17.582
[laughs] MINGYU assaulted SEUNGKWAN!

40:17.665 --> 40:19.250
That's how he warms up. Ah! Ah! Ah!

40:19.334 --> 40:20.835
-[laughter]
-[S.COUPS] What was that?

40:20.919 --> 40:21.920
What now?

40:22.003 --> 40:23.838
-SEUNGKWAN's warm-up.
-When he warms up.

40:23.922 --> 40:26.257
[all] Ah! Ah! Ah!

40:26.341 --> 40:29.218
I felt relieved and elated.

40:29.302 --> 40:33.681
I was just happy
to be there with my members.

40:34.307 --> 40:35.683
That was how I felt.

40:35.767 --> 40:37.060
I honestly had fun.

40:40.396 --> 40:42.106
[♪ SEVENTEEN "HOME" playing]

40:42.190 --> 40:45.610
MINGYU

40:51.658 --> 40:53.493
♪ What can I do? ♪

40:53.576 --> 40:54.577
[crowd cheering]

40:54.661 --> 40:56.621
♪ When you aren't around ♪

40:56.704 --> 41:00.583
♪ My heart stops cold
like a beat-up robot ♪

41:00.667 --> 41:04.003
[DINO] As I sing our song,
completely immersed in the moment,

41:06.255 --> 41:08.800
the audience is shouting their hearts out.

41:08.883 --> 41:13.638
♪ It must be as tough for you too
What can we do? Yeah ♪

41:14.180 --> 41:16.683
♪ Baby, I want to keep our warmth ♪

41:16.766 --> 41:19.519
♪ Just the way it is ♪

41:19.602 --> 41:22.313
I thought, "What a great life I have."

41:22.397 --> 41:25.441
♪ Can't undo what we have here ♪

41:25.525 --> 41:27.652
[DK] It was uncanny yet somehow moving.

41:27.735 --> 41:30.780
♪ Tell me something, anything ♪

41:30.863 --> 41:33.074
♪ I'm struggling to get through to you ♪

41:33.157 --> 41:34.993
♪ I suddenly get scared ♪

41:35.076 --> 41:38.871
♪ What can I do?
When you aren't around ♪

41:38.955 --> 41:41.958
It was amazing,
as if my imagination had come to life.

41:42.041 --> 41:46.295
♪ I don't have nowhere to return to
My heart stays empty for you ♪

41:46.379 --> 41:48.089
♪ In a way ♪

41:48.172 --> 41:51.801
[JOSHUA] If the audience had fun,
that would mean it was perfect.

41:53.011 --> 41:56.055
We need to stay imperfect
to leave room for growth.

41:56.139 --> 41:58.141
That's the fun of it.

41:58.224 --> 42:00.810
That must be the essence of a great show.

42:02.270 --> 42:06.190
[in English] ♪ 'Cause I'm your home,
home, home, home ♪

42:07.817 --> 42:11.738
♪ 'Cause I'm your home, home, home, home ♪

42:13.156 --> 42:17.493
[in Korean] It feels great to see a song
being well received by the audience.

42:19.662 --> 42:21.080
[JOSHUA] CARATs. [chuckles]

42:21.164 --> 42:22.206
[fans screaming]

42:22.290 --> 42:26.919
Ah, I'm so happy today,
thanks to all of you, CARATs. I mean it.

42:27.003 --> 42:30.131
I'm so grateful that
I got to meet our CARATs,

42:30.214 --> 42:31.924
and I feel very blessed.

42:32.008 --> 42:37.138
At times, we may fall down,
but SEVENTEEN will overcome everything.

42:37.221 --> 42:41.392
Stay healthy until we're back together
as a team of 13.

42:42.060 --> 42:43.061
Everyone.

42:44.645 --> 42:45.897
Thank you!

42:45.980 --> 42:47.982
[crowd cheering]

42:49.192 --> 42:53.988
♪ My feelings for you
seem to have surpassed yours now ♪

42:54.072 --> 42:58.159
♪ I'm not saying your feelings are small ♪

42:58.993 --> 43:03.289
♪ Yeah, it's still cold out
And so is the tip of my nose ♪

43:03.372 --> 43:05.792
[WOOZI] I just know
we'll put on a great show

43:05.875 --> 43:09.128
when we set foot on the stage.

43:09.754 --> 43:10.755
Yes.

43:12.006 --> 43:14.801
If we get on the stage,
meet our fans in good health,

43:14.884 --> 43:18.471
and spend time together,
then that is a great show.

43:19.555 --> 43:21.516
♪ I suddenly get scared ♪

43:21.599 --> 43:24.727
♪ What can I do?
When you aren't around ♪

43:24.811 --> 43:27.772
[DINO] I become more grateful
and start to have even more fun

43:27.855 --> 43:31.317
when I interact with the audience,
with CARATs from the stage.

43:32.485 --> 43:36.572
♪ In a way, it may be hard ♪

43:37.573 --> 43:41.911
♪ But I'm always standing here
No pressure ♪

43:42.620 --> 43:44.122
♪ I don't want to let you ♪

43:44.205 --> 43:47.625
I begin to think, "It was fun.
I didn't know I was like this."

43:47.708 --> 43:53.798
♪ I don't want to be scared every day
With this broken heart ♪

43:55.174 --> 43:56.384
I feel much lighter.

43:56.467 --> 43:57.927
It was another great day.

43:58.761 --> 44:01.556
Another one tomorrow?
I'll do a great job tomorrow too.

44:01.639 --> 44:03.015
[crowd cheering]

44:03.099 --> 44:04.767
THANK YOU FOR YOUR WONDERFUL MUSIC

44:04.851 --> 44:08.771
[in English] ♪ Cause I'm your home,
home, home, home ♪

44:08.855 --> 44:11.399
♪ Home, home, home, home ♪

44:13.109 --> 44:17.071
♪ Cause I'm your home, home, home, home

44:18.114 --> 44:21.284
♪ Because you're my home,
home, home, home ♪

44:21.367 --> 44:25.997
[WONWOO in Korean] I often see a good
rapport forming between CARATs and us.

44:28.624 --> 44:29.667
I'm filled with pride.

44:30.293 --> 44:32.170
-[♪ music ends]
-[crowd cheering]

44:32.253 --> 44:34.630
[WONWOO] I even think,
"I'm glad I decided to do music."

44:37.884 --> 44:43.097
[staff] What do you think you've gained
and lost as a member of SEVENTEEN?

44:43.681 --> 44:48.561
[WOOZI] Basically, everything I gained
is thanks to being a part of SEVENTEEN.

44:49.478 --> 44:51.230
Who I am,

44:52.315 --> 44:54.525
these thoughts I have right now,

44:55.693 --> 44:57.862
the music we release,

44:57.945 --> 44:59.697
CARATs, our members,

44:59.780 --> 45:03.993
and everyone in my life,
I gained through SEVENTEEN.

45:04.076 --> 45:09.081
If I were to point out
something I seemingly lost,

45:09.165 --> 45:13.252
it'd probably be things like
living an ordinary life and all,

45:13.336 --> 45:15.254
but in a way, it's still a gain.

45:15.963 --> 45:18.591
I got to have all those things.

45:20.676 --> 45:22.678
[♪ upbeat jazz music playing]

45:27.141 --> 45:29.560
[♪ SEVENTEEN "Together"
playing over speakers]

45:42.323 --> 45:44.951
[♪ SEVENTEEN "Cheers to youth"
playing over speakers]

45:55.836 --> 45:58.047
[♪ SEVENTEEN "Super"
playing over speakers]

45:58.631 --> 46:00.049
[HYELIM] Wow!

46:00.132 --> 46:01.217
[HOSHI yells]

46:06.889 --> 46:08.307
I was the first to come in.

46:10.059 --> 46:12.520
I think this is the first time
since our debut.

46:13.813 --> 46:14.981
I can't quite believe it.

46:15.564 --> 46:17.984
I'm only two minutes early.

46:18.067 --> 46:19.568
S.COUPS better not be late.

46:23.823 --> 46:25.449
[♪ upbeat jazz music continues]

46:25.533 --> 46:26.909
[S.COUPS] I can't take them off.

46:30.663 --> 46:33.165
Did my feet put on weight? [laughs]

46:34.834 --> 46:36.419
This pair is quite old.

46:39.672 --> 46:42.425
[♪ SEVENTEEN "LOVE, MONEY, FAME"
playing over speakers]

46:48.264 --> 46:50.433
Hey, we didn't do our cheer today!

46:52.727 --> 46:54.228
We didn't do it!

46:54.312 --> 46:55.730
[all] One, two, three.

46:55.813 --> 46:56.939
Let's go!

46:57.023 --> 46:58.649
"Bittersweet," let's do it!

46:59.608 --> 47:01.027
♪ Nothing ♪

47:02.403 --> 47:03.779
We didn't do our cheer today.

47:03.863 --> 47:05.156
[members in Japanese] We love you.

47:05.239 --> 47:06.240
[fans screaming]

47:06.324 --> 47:08.534
[members in Korean]
One, two, three. Let's go!

47:08.617 --> 47:10.953
[crowd cheering]

47:11.037 --> 47:12.663
[members in English]
SEVENTEEN, RIGHT HERE!

47:13.748 --> 47:14.832
[♪ upbeat jazz music ends]

47:14.915 --> 47:16.917
Subtitle translation by Eun Sook Youn
